cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a caching scheme that utilizes coding techniques to reduce backhaul traffic in wireless networks. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on device-to-device communication networks and proposes caching schemes to reduce traffic during peak times. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed caching scheme where users cache popular content in their devices. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper considers a scenario where some users exhibit selfish behavior and do not share their cache content with others. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions online video streaming as a major contributor to backhaul traffic, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
